    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>April 19 article about questions surrounding adequacy of background checks for gun buyers in wake of massacre at Virginia Polytechnic Institute incorrectly described meaning of Virginia's being 'shall issue' state; term refers to qualifications for obtaining permit to carry concealed weapon</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Thursday about questions surrounding the adequacy of background checks for gun buyers in the wake of the massacre at Virginia Polytechnic Institute incorrectly described the meaning of Virginia's being a ''shall issue'' state. The term refers to the qualifications for obtaining a permit to carry a concealed weapon, not for obtaining a weapon.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article on Thursday about questions surrounding the adequacy of background checks for gun buyers in the wake of the massacre at Virginia Polytechnic Institute incorrectly described the meaning of Virginia's being a ''shall issue'' state. The term refers to the qualifications for obtaining a permit to carry a concealed weapon, not for obtaining a weapon.</p>
      </block>
